                    <comment id="13180531" author="simonw" created="Thu, 5 Jan 2012 17:06:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;here is a patch that merges multiple SortedSources on the fly using in MultiDocValues. This allows to use SlowMRW etc. even with sorted DocValue variants. I cut back to use SlowMRW if needed in TestSort and TestTypePromotion and added a testcase to TestDocValuesIndexing to assert sorting etc. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also generalized SortedBytesMergeUtils and used it in MultiDocValues to implement the on-the-fly merging.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;all tests pass &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;20&quot; width=&quot;20&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; yay!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13181446" author="simonw" created="Fri, 6 Jan 2012 17:16:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will commit this if nobody objects&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
